The app now has a mix of older and newer trend/history flows. This needs to become one clean system.

Focus now:
- bring Keto metrics fully onto the newer dedicated per-metric trend screen model
- standardize graph → history → edit behavior across Keto, Health, and Exercise where supported
- keep manual Ember values taking display priority over imported values where applicable
- clean up the metric-history `+` flow so all supported metrics use the correct metric-specific manual-entry popup/sheet
- preserve working history screens without redesigning them unnecessarily
- apply semantic graph colors by metric family
- improve trend/date UX without introducing yet another trend architecture

Current follow-up notes:
- Weight history `+` popup was fixed, but the generalized metric-history add flow still needs to be made consistent
